8) We cannot think of a better way to begin this re-evaluation than to hold an exhibition of this wonderful and cherished Collection to a wider and hopefully, new audience.
7) 30 years have passed since the death of Maurice Wade and now we feel it is only right for his work and his place in 20th century Modern British Art to undergo a long overdue reappraisal.

6) The 21 paintings in the McCluskey collection will also be accompanied by 30, never before seen, Maurice Wade drawings. The Exhibition will open on Friday 25th February 2022 with a book signing attended by Andy on Saturday 26th February 2022

5) In addition to the book there is also a luxury limited edition box set limited to 100 copies. This set contains a number of additional items relating to the publication and the exhibition. This also is available to purchase from today on pre-order from our website.
4) The book, entitled, Maurice Wade, Silent Landscapes - The Andy McCluskey Collection is available for pre-order from 11.00am today on our website.

3) The paintings belong to musician and founder member of the electronic band Orchestral Manoeuvres in the Dark (OMD), Andy McCluskey. To accompany the exhibition there will a luxuriously produced 80-page book with sumptuous illustrations, printed & bound by Gomer Press of Wales

2) We have been working hard behind the scenes to bring a very special exhibition to fruition. The event of Covid 19 impacted our plans greatly, however, today we are delighted to announce that in February 2022 we will be holding an exhibition of Maurice Wade paintings.

 https://t.co/3i5RiC2Y9s

One day my prince will come! Wait. No. What I really want is a break from work so I can learn how to #knit, like the rest of my friends right now. Oh yeah, and so I can write new #TiaraTuesday blog posts. But for now, a repurposed one will have to do. https://t.co/MFKVOFILP9 https://t.co/ykP0QMQ7tx

It's #Friday! We should celebrate! Let's revisit another Famous Jewelry In The #Movies article from the website, shall we? I remember loving "How To Lose a Guy In Ten Days" when it came out. And the fact that #jewelry played a major role? Bonus! https://t.co/EjESYMcxDF https://t.co/vygherPuPN

Oh the 1940's. They started out tough - #WWII was hard on almost everyone - but they ended with a bang! All of which makes for some varied #engagmentring motifs. Who got engaged in the '40s and what did the rings look like? #WeddingWednesday 👰 https://t.co/3ZUQsM9ziJ https://t.co/OOIJU9IQaC

#Queen Mary was a woman after my own ♥️. That lady LOVED jewelry like it was her job. The current Queen wore a not often seen brooch that belonged to Mary this week, so I thought we'd revisit one of Mary's #tiaras. But do you know what happened to it? 👸 https://t.co/ySCo1XHVCs https://t.co/DAIM92vYk6

Oh the #1950s! Poodle skirts, sock hops, soda jerks and #Hollywood movie stars that were almost god and goddess like. And #engagementrings, many of which took a fun/funky turn in the 50's (hint: #ElizabethTaylor makes another cameo). #WeddingWednesday 👰 https://t.co/uZzIWN4YzA https://t.co/pEp3hZCMX2

What day of the week is it?! I honestly didn’t realize it was #TiaraTuesday. So, let’s revisit the The Grand #Duchess Vladimir #Tiara. It has one heck of a story.Which team are you on (you'll understand when you read the post)?  👑 #Royalfamily
https://t.co/aEKnAaOs0a https://t.co/IBmZvJNCR1
